Killer Tip: Excel 4.0

PROBLEM: You need to display cells in thousands of dollars yet retain
their actual values.

SOLUTION: Select the cells to reformat. Next select Format, Number. Pick
a suitable form from the list, say #,##0. Select the Code box at the
bottom of the dialog box, put acomma at the end of the format so that it
looks like #,##0, and press OK.

Each extra comma after a number format displays the number as if it had
been divided by 1,000.

